  "prompt": "I scored 72% in 10th and 88% in 12 can I be able to became ias officer?",
  "response": "Yes, scoring 72% in your 10th and 88% in your 12th grades does not prevent you from becoming an IAS (Indian Administrative Service) officer. The eligibility to become an IAS officer mainly involves clearing the Civil Services Examination (CSE) conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in India. The basic criteria for eligibility include:\n\n1. **Educational Qualification**: You must have a graduate degree from a recognized university in any discipline. The marks you obtained in 10th or 12th grades do not affect your eligibility.\n\n2. **Age Limit**: As of the date of examination, candidates must be at least 21 years of age and not more than 32 years of age for the general category. There are age relaxations for reserved categories.\n\n3. **Nationality**: You must be a citizen of India.\n\n4. **Attempts**: The number of attempts allowed for general category candidates is six. There are more attempts allowed for candidates from reserved categories.\n\nTo become an IAS officer, you need to demonstrate diligence, hard work, and a deep understanding of the subjects covered in the UPSC exams, which include multiple papers in various subjects. It requires preparation and dedication, but your previous high school percentages do not limit your potential for this career path.",
